#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Fixes the real root cause of the "River May A" (and similar) stuck fallback
lyrics: some MIDI files store an entire verse as ONE single Text event
instead of one event per word. Nothing earlier in the pipeline could split
a line like that -- groupIntoLines only ever breaks *between* separate
events, and a single event has nothing to break between. It also isn't
caught by the "fetch lyrics online instead" fallback, because that only
triggers when the MIDI produced *zero* lines -- one giant line still
counts as "found lyrics," so the unsplittable block was used as-is.

This adds a final splitting pass (MidiLyricParser.splitLongLines) that
runs on the finished line list regardless of source (MIDI or online), and
wires it into KaraokePlayerActivity right after lines are sorted.

Usage (run from the repo root, e.g. ~/PureNeroflix in Termux):
    python3 apply_stuck_line_fix.py

Overwrites MidiLyricParser.java and KaraokePlayerActivity.java in place.
No git/patch tooling required.
"""
import os
import sys

